q3n (1.1.3-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix: list_entries filters by extension before content-scanning (no more slow home dir scans)
  * Fix: detect() skips files larger than scan_max_bytes (default 10MB, was 1MB)
  * Fix: q3n run fortune exits cleanly with usage message when no entries loaded
  * GUI: plugin dock now loads on startup (fortune/cite panels visible immediately)
  * GUI: inline URI validation label in EntryDetailView (live ✓/⚠ feedback per scheme)
  * GUI: Tools > Validate URIs... menu shows per-entry validation report
  * GUI: remember_last_file option reopens last open file on startup
  * Add: user config system (~/.config/q3n/q3n.conf) with scan_max_bytes,
         default_export_format, style_file, remember_last_file, extra_dirs,
         default_citation_style
  * Add: user theming via ~/.config/q3n/style.qss (Qt stylesheet, full control)
  * Add: plugin QSS cascade — fortune/cite panels styled via main QSS (themeable)
  * Add: q3n config subcommand (--show, --edit, --install, --force)
  * Add: AppStream metadata installed to /usr/share/metainfo/
  * Fix: q3n export -f now accepts all 7 formats (html, index, fortune were missing)
  * Fix: setup.py license classifier replaced with SPDX expression
  * Docs: ARCHITECTURE.md, CLAUDE.md, specification.md, man page fully updated

